article.headline: Kent State 96, Notre Dame College o 80
article.linkText: Kent State 96, Notre Dame College o 80
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- DeAndre Haynes scored 14 points and passed for 12 assists to lead Kent State to a 96-80 victory over Notre Dame College on Wednesday. The Golden Flashes (8-2) placed five players in double figures and shot 56 percent from the field. Kevin Warzynski had 18 points and Nate Gerwig made 8 of 8 shots to finish with 17. Jerome Pierce made 5 of 9 3-pointers and scored 23 points for the Falcons (7-7), who outrebounded Kent State 34-31. Dave Hilborn added 22 points. The two teams were tied at 33 with 5:41 left in the first half but the Golden Flashes responded with a 9-2 run. Haynes finished it off with a 3-pointer. Kent State then opened up the second half with a 14-0 run to take control. A layup from Warzynski made it 67-45 with 16:24 left. Jason Edwin also had 14 points for the Golden Flashes while Notre Dame's Paul Benjamin had 15 points and six rebounds.
